===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
Uncertain. Various explanations include:
* According to the {{w|Shuowen}}, {{Han compound|八|亏|t1=division|t2=exhaled air}} — the smooth flow of speech.
* {{Han compound|ls=psc|釆|二|c1=p|c2=s|t2=two equal lines}} ([[Wiktionary:About Chinese/references#L|Lin Yiguang, 1920]])
* A {{liushu|p|nocap=y}} of [[waterweed]] spread flat on the surface of water. Original form of {{och-l|苹|duckweed}}. (Lawrence J. Howell)
* {{liushu|p}} of a balance scale. ({{w|Bernhard Karlgren|Karlgren}},  1973)

===Etymology===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*(p/b)ljaŋ|t=plank; palm; flat surface; wing}}, whence {{cog|kac|phun-pyen|tr=phun⁵⁵ pjen³³|t=plank}} and {{cog|my|ပျဉ်|t=flat board}} (STEDT).

